#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""``alfred``: operator CLI for the alfred-os fleet.

A small, dependency-free entry point covering the operator's day-to-day
verbs. Heavy logic lives in ``lib/agent_runner.py``; this file is just
arg-parsing and pretty-printing.

Subcommands today:

  alfred agents               List configured agents from ``agents.conf``
                              with role, schedule, resolved enable state,
                              and whether the host scheduler currently has
                              the unit loaded.
  alfred pause <codename|all> Stop scheduled firings for an agent. Writes a
                              marker at ``$ALFRED_HOME/state/_paused/<name>``
                              so the pause survives ``deploy.sh``, then
                              unloads the unit from the host scheduler
                              (launchd on macOS, systemd --user on Linux).
                              Already-running firings are not killed.
  alfred resume <codename|all>
                              Reverse a pause: remove the marker and reload
                              the unit. No-op if the agent was not paused.
  alfred run <codename>       Kick a single agent now (one-shot), killing
                              any in-flight firing first. Honors the pause
                              marker unless ``--force`` is passed.
  alfred dry-run <codename>   Bypass the scheduler and simulate one firing.
                              Pass ``--native`` to execute supported runners
                              with ALFRED_DRY_RUN=1.
  alfred enable <codename>    Add ``codename`` to the runner-level fleet
                              gate file.
                              Idempotent.
  alfred disable <codename>   Remove ``codename`` from the runner-level
                              fleet gate file. Idempotent.
  alfred enabled-agents       Print the parsed list of enabled codenames
                              (or explain that the gate file is missing).
  alfred engine status [agent]
                              Show resolved Claude/Codex engine mode for one
                              agent or the configured LLM runner fleet.
  alfred engine set <agent> <claude|codex|hybrid>
                              Persist an engine override in
                              $ALFRED_HOME/state/engines/<agent>.
                              Alias: provider.
  alfred codex [status|probe] Show Codex CLI availability and run a tiny
                              non-interactive probe.
  alfred auth [status|probe]  Check Claude Code and Codex CLI auth surfaces.
  alfred claude [status|primary|secondary|swap|probe]
                              Show or change the Claude account used by
                              scheduled agents.
  alfred status               Show local fleet health, locks, pauses, and
                              approval waits.
  alfred doctor               Run host preflight checks for the configured
                              fleet without burning engine turns.
  alfred pr check <number>    Report whether a PR passes the GitHub-native
                              merge gate (approved on GitHub, threads resolved,
                              mergeable + clean, no failing checks). Read-only.
  alfred pr merge <number>    Merge a PR only if it passes that same gate,
                              using a SHA-guarded squash. Pass --repo for a
                              specific repo. See docs/MERGE_GATE.md.
  alfred metrics              Weekly per-agent firings/cost/turns/tool-use
                              roll-up across spend, transcripts, and Codex
                              artifacts.
  alfred benchmark            Reproducible self-benchmark from existing
                              telemetry: throughput, quality, reliability,
                              efficiency, and % of plan quota per PR.
  alfred logs <codename>      Inspect stream-JSON transcripts for one agent:
                              recent firings, tool-call summary, or a full
                              pretty-printed dump of one firing.
  alfred brain ...            Inspect and seed the local fleet-brain memory
                              layer (`status`, `lessons`, `reflect`,
                              `governor`, `failure-patterns`, `firings`,
                              `forget`, `export`).
  alfred memory doctor        Inspect the unified memory plane: provider chain,
                              Redis AMS, FleetBrain, code-memory, code-map,
                              and read-only MCP tool exposure.
  alfred goal ...             Manage the durable goal ledger (`create`,
                              `list`, `status`, `approve`, `pause`,
                              `resume`, `clear`).
  alfred code-memory ...      Inspect, index, or serve the optional
                              code-structure memory MCP layer.
  alfred code-map ...         Build/export/query Alfred's local JSON code
                              graph using the stable alfred-codegraph@1
                              contract.
  alfred capabilities         Inspect local code graph, token, and skill
                              capabilities Alfred can use during setup.
  alfred demo                 Watch the whole loop (plan, approve, build,
                              review that catches a planted bug, fix, ship)
                              on a throwaway sample repo in about a minute.
                              Needs only an authenticated `claude` CLI: no
                              GitHub, no Slack, no tokens.
  alfred serve                Open the read-only localhost dashboard over
                              fleet state and reliability-governor actions.
  alfred slack-listener       Run the Slack-native planning listener, or
                              process one event with `once`.
  alfred slack-thread-sync    Post fleet progress (issue claimed, PR opened,
                              CI pass/fail, merged) back to the Slack thread
                              that filed each issue. Read-only on GitHub;
                              posts only the delta since the last sweep.
  alfred shipped              Summarize merged PRs, issues, LOC, and
                              model/config changes. ``--self-proof`` reports the
                              share of merged PRs shipped by Alfred agents.
  alfred telemetry ...        Inspect or change anonymous usage totals.
  alfred skills ...           Manage curated skill packs (`list`,
                              `install <pack>`, `installed`). Vendored packs
                              copy in offline; reference-install packs fetch
                              from source and need `--yes`.

The runner-level fleet gate file lives at
``$ALFRED_HOME/state/fleet/enabled.txt``. Listed codenames are enabled.
Missing codenames fall back to each runner's default: stable agents are
default-enabled, while opt-in agents such as the architect default to disabled
until explicitly enabled.

Pure stdlib. The operator reads this file when something breaks; keep
it that way, with no external dependencies.
"""

from __future__ import annotations

